:QUOTE [subtitle:Ralph Ellison, quotetype:PLAIN]
I am an invisible man. Not a ghost, though some people believe I might be.

:JOURNEY
Reading Invisible Man
Section
Impact
- Battle Royal chapter | 5 | Novel in miniature
- College chapters | 4 | Institutional racism
- Brotherhood sections | 5 | Idealism and limits
- Harlem riot | 5 | Earns everything | The ending justifies every page of what came before

:IMAGE
cover.jpg

:NOTE
This is not an easy novel. It is a rewarding one. The difference is that \
difficulty here is proportional to what the novel is trying to do, and what \
it is trying to do is among the most important things American fiction has attempted.

:POLL
Do you think Invisible Man is the most important American novel of the twentieth century?
Yes without reservation
One of the most important but I would name another alongside it
I have not read enough to have a confident view
I have not read it yet
